CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper January 25, 1947, pg. 10, reads: "They Leave You Spellbound - Four of a kind, the Spellbinders Quartette [Quartet] includes talented (left to right) Margaret Leavelle, Pauline Branson, Revella Tunie and Frances Leavelle, who will be one of the feature attractions of the Talent Night program at St. James AME Church Friday, Jan. 24, at 8 P.M. The charming singers are all employed at The Pittsburgh Courier. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Courier newspaper employees and members of the Spellbinders Quartet: Margaret Leavelle, Pauline Branson, Revella Tunie, and Frances Leavelle, posed in Courier office
